OL,7,FThe statement went on to say the club
OL,8,Fhas a "zero-tolerance" attitude
OL,9,Ftowards discrimination and abuse, and
OL,10,Fthat it was working with Merseyside
OL,11,FPolice and the Premier League to find
OL,12,Fthe individuals concerned and hold
OL,13,Fthem accountable for their actions.
OL,15,F"Threats or abuse of any kind -
OL,16,Fwhether on-line or in person - are
OL,17,Fcompletely unacceptable and have no
OL,18,Fplace in our game or in society," the
OL,19,Fstatement, posted on X, added.
